  "text": ", where ↑ and ↓ indicate a site occupied by up and down spins, respectively, • indicates an empty site, XX =↑↓ + ↓↑, and the ellipsis denotes the repetition of a given root configuration. Each of these four root configurations has a six-fold degeneracy via the center-of-mass shift, altogether generating 24 degenerate states. Note that the root configurations of the Halperin (551) state can be constructed similarly to those of the Halperin (331) state [CITATION_1] .",
