  "bib_entries": {
    "45033847": {
      "title": "Halperin (m, m ′ , n) bilayer quantum Hall states on thin cylinders",
      "abstract": "The Halperin (m,m',n) bilayer quantum Hall states are studied on thin cylinders. In this limit, charge-density-wave patterns emerge that are characteristic of the underlying quantum Hall state. The general patterns are worked out from a variant of the plasma analogy. Torus degeneracies are recovered, and for some important special cases a connection to well-known spin chain physics is made. By including interlayer tunneling, we also work out the critical behavior of a possible phase transition between the (331) state and the non-Abelian Moore-Read state in the thin cylinder limit."
    }
